# Readmes are part of the delivery

Do **not** wait for the user to ask. After behavioural or architectural code changes, sync the docs in `readme/`.

## Before implementing

1. Identify which specs apply (`SPEC_WEB_STORE.md`, `SPEC_ADMIN.md`, `SPEC_INFRASTRUCTURE.md`, `open_*.md`, etc.).
2. Skim the relevant sections so the change matches documented intent (or update the docs if intent changed).

## After implementing

Update every readme that would otherwise become wrong or incomplete. Typical triggers:

| Change | Readmes to touch |
|--------|------------------|
| Store auth / cookie / session / login routes | `SPEC_WEB_STORE.md`, `SPEC_ADMIN.md`, `SPEC_INFRASTRUCTURE.md`, `open_UPDATES.md` |
| Admin auth / roles / staff vs customer | `SPEC_ADMIN.md`, `SPEC_INFRASTRUCTURE.md` |
| Azure / Blazor / WebSockets / deploy | `SPEC_INFRASTRUCTURE.md` |
| Checkout / Mollie / stock | `SPEC_WEB_STORE.md`, `open_MOLLIE_PAYMENTS.md`, stock/roadmap opens |
| UI / nav / store chrome decisions | `open_UPDATES.md`, `SPEC_WEB_STORE.md` |

## How to update

- Change the **current-state** tables/sections; mark obsolete claims clearly (e.g. `> [!IMPORTANT]`).
- Prefer short factual amendments over long new essays.
- Add a dated one-liner to `open_UPDATES.md` when the runtime diverges from older UI notes.
- Do not invent ERP columns or features in docs that are not in code.

## Done check

Code shipped without matching readme updates for the areas above = incomplete.
